Research suggests that older fathers may contribute to an increased risk of schizophrenia in their children, with over 15% of cases possibly linked to paternal age over 30.
Concern over cannabis use in French teenagers has led to a 10-million euro campaign highlighting its harmful effects.
Australian researchers have made progress in understanding schizophrenia, linking impaired thought processes to brain structure.
Icelandic researchers have identified a genetic region in Europeans that may impact fertility and longevity.
Additionally, a study in Uganda emphasizes the social and economic impact of mental illness.
